result.name: Tao Heung

reviews.text: Inside hang fa chuen shopping arcade, this restaurant has very comfy seating and offers delicious food with reasonable price tag. It is recommendable for anybody who live nearby to try the foods here.

Inconsistent food quality and always lack of sufficient staff, and if available, not attentive to customers’ need. Typically interrupting customers’ conversations as they like to talk to their regular customers who are usually elderly residents of the residential estate, ignoring the needs of those attending the meals at the same table. 

Sometimes the hard-selling of certain higher priced dim-sum or special packages of cakes or dumplings during local festivals could be very annoying and interrupting conversations of their customers even after they have shown no interest. Prices are general quite low especially during weekdays and more so for lunch and afternoon-tea periods. Retirees would find it a good place to meet up with old friends and family gatherings.
It provides half prices for dim sum as breakfast when customers check the bills before 11am on weekdays. It's a very good idea for early birds!
I can feel the MSG in the food

result.name: Paradise Mall

reviews.text:
There's a sports equipment outlet in the mall. There are a variety of restaurants, but personally I don't really like them. 梅光軒, 八方雲集, Paradise is good though. 😅

The mall is linked with the MTR mall, and it's close to the playgrounds nearby. 😀

Quiet a range of food and clothing choices, with very spatial, comfortable circulation. Paid a short visit with my family at a Chinese Restaurant. Happy with there quality food at a very affordable price. It could have been better with a wider selection of dim sum.

The top floors are outlets of sports shoes and fashion.  You can find most brands here.  Some offers bulk discounts from time to time and the merchandise can become extraordinary inexpensive subject to you buying lots lots lots.
This is a all-round mall with all kinds of shops. A few outlet shops there and the only indoor bouldering gym in a mall in HK makes this mall worth going

Truly like a paradis with many goody shops and a Tao Heung restaurant where I eat fatty beef, fish ball, sausage, luncheon meat, shrimp, dumpling, pork slice, noodol, ouster, clam (ent), wif garlic, chiuchow chili, soy sauce and some paste with 2 Pepsi. But no beer. Enjoy a calebrating time with friends

result.name: 稻香

reviews.text: 服務態度差。唔覺意比左間房我地坐，但原來唔比人關門，咁咪不停開開關關咁。最後有位侍應推開門，一句唔講，仲要瞄嘴先走。火都黎埋。
食物，環境都可以，飲廣東茶幾好享受
服務水平一般，不過性價比還算不錯
地方乾淨，食品好味，份量偏小，假期要等位，價格普通不貴。
有自助定食火煱，只可食2小時，有6:30 pm - 8:30 pm 及 8:30 pm - 10:30 pm。但發覺6: 30 pm 時段很多空置枱，但一進入8:30 pm, 有好多客人湧入。原因前時段要$198, 而尾時係$138.-。而我光顧海鮮火煱，即自己選擇任何食物用來火煱，三人食，七佰元也不需。都算抵食。
